This paper is about measuring the speed of evolutionary algorithm operations in different programming languages, which falls under the category of computational intelligence (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper compares interpreted and compiled languages, which could also fit under programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also involves performance evaluation (cs.DC) and machine learning (cs.LG) since evolutionary algorithms are a type of machine learning algorithm.
